Outer Class

- cannot be private, protected, static
- can be public, default and abstract

Inner Class

- can be public, private, protected, default, final, static and abstract.

Abstract Class

- can be public, abstract and default

Interface

- can be public, abstract, and default

Methods

- can be public, private, protected, default, abstract, final and static

Local Variables

- Will always be same as method within which they are defined by default and we cannot change it access scope.
- They can be final, but not static and abstract

Instance Variables
- Can be public, private, protected, default, final and static, but cannot be abstract.

class Variables

- Can be public, private, protected, default and final, but cannot be abstract.